---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="What data leaves your browser when you use this site, where it goes, and what control you have over it."
>
  <main class="vr-shell vr-stub">
    <div class="vr-stub__row" data-reveal>
      <span class="vr-eyebrow">— Privacy ⁄ §00</span>
      <div class="vr-prose">
        <h1 class="vr-h2">Privacy.</h1>
        <p class="vr-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p class="vr-body">
          This is a one-person engineering practice. The aim of this page is
          to tell you, in plain language, what data leaves your browser when
          you use this site, where it goes, and what control you have over
          it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">What I collect.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          <strong>Email addresses you give me.</strong> If you join the
          course waitlist, your email is sent to my email service provider
          (MailerLite) and tagged to a specific list. I will use it to
          contact you about the course and nothing else. I won't sell or
          share it.
        </p>
        <p class="vr-body">
          <strong>Booking information.</strong> When you book a call, the
          form is provided by Cal.com. The information you submit (name,
          email, scheduling details, payment) is processed by Cal.com and
          their payment provider, Stripe. I receive the booking and the
          email address; I do not see, store, or have access to your card
          details.
        </p>
        <p class="vr-body">
          <strong>Server logs.</strong> Cloudflare records standard request
          metadata (IP, user agent, request path) for the site and uses it
          for protecting the site against abuse. I do not store these logs
          beyond Cloudflare's defaults.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">What I do not collect.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          No analytics scripts. No advertising trackers. No fingerprinting.
          No third-party cookies set by this site directly.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Third parties.</h2>
        <ul class="vr-prose__list">
          <li>
            <strong>MailerLite</strong> — stores email addresses for the
            waitlist. <a href="https://www.mailerlite.com/legal/privacy-policy">Their privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cal.com</strong> — handles scheduling and the booking
            form. <a href="https://cal.com/privacy">Their privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Stripe</strong> — processes the booking deposit, via
            Cal.com. <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy">Their privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosts the site and provides
            security. <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Their privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Fonts</strong> — serves typefaces. Loading a
            page issues a request to fonts.gstatic.com.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Your rights.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          If you're in a jurisdiction with data-protection laws (EU/UK
          GDPR, California CCPA, etc.), you have the right to access,
          correct, or delete the personal data I hold about you. Email
          <a href="mailto:hello@valkyrieremedy.com">hello@valkyrieremedy.com</a>
          and I'll handle it within 30 days. To unsubscribe from the
          waitlist directly, every email I send through MailerLite has a
          one-click unsubscribe.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Changes.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          If this policy changes materially, I'll update the date at the
          top and note the change. For the avoidance of doubt: this is a
          working draft authored by a non-lawyer; for binding language
          consult a professional. If you spot a problem with the policy,
          email me.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .vr-stub {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding-block: 4rem 6rem;
  }
  .vr-stub__row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(120px, 200px) 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
    padding-block: 2rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .vr-stub__row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  }
  .vr-prose {
    max-width: 78ch;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .vr-prose .vr-body { max-width: none; margin: 0; }
  .vr-prose__h {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--vr-serif);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--vr-step-2);
    color: var(--vr-bone);
  }
  .vr-prose__list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--vr-bone-dim);
    font-family: var(--vr-serif-body);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .vr-prose a {
    color: var(--vr-gold);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .vr-prose a:hover { color: var(--vr-iron-warm); }
</style>
